# CONVERT METERS TO KILOMETERS
# You will be given an integer that will be distance in meters. Write a program that converts meters to
# kilometers formatted to the second decimal point.

# SOLUTION
# Read the meters from the console.

meters = int(input())

# Divide the meters by 1000 and round up to the second decimal place using ":.2f".
# Print out the result.

kilometers = meters / 1000
print(f'{kilometers:.2f}')
